The paper proposes a new type of neural network, specifically a hyperbolic graph convolutional neural network (HGCN), which is designed to embed nodes in a graph into hyperbolic space. This paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new type of neural network architecture. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a new method for learning node representations in graphs. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves developing a new type of neural network. It could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves learning representations of nodes in graphs. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves developing a new method for representing and analyzing graphs.
